Mixed bag of stuff on that list, but a lot of it sounds like necros in groups and raids wanting to help out more in those settings.  Me, I'd rather be doing damage in a group, so I suggested more high damage/low duration DOTs and voted for the debuff slot increase.  A nuke would be ok, but what we're crying for is not to be stuck as the twitch bitch anymore. However, it sounds like there's plenty of necros used to doing that anyway.

As for the group life/mana heals, I suggested they might be suited better for a shaman type of spell.  I was also against the AA rez, suggesting instead if anyone gets the ability to rez with ease it should be the shaman.

To me, the necromancer should be more about inpiring terror, causing damage with decay and pain, and commanding the undead.  I lean more towards the offensive abilities for necros, and would rather see the group bonuses and rezzes go to the shaman.  Necros sacrifice their life blood to create destruction and death for their own personal gain, while shamans give it up to help their "tribe".

